TopicTitle: Anyone know of any good N1 reference material?

Articles.Content:
So I'm working on a 3d model of the N1.

The only problem is that I can't seem to find any decent references for it. Besides a few basic schematics all I have managed to find is a few pictures, all of which are grainy and/or overexposed to some degree.

https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/22015656/N1/5160175400_950fc23159_o.jpg

https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/22015656/N1/5160226764_632d14f60f_o.jpg

It's good enough to make out some the rough stuff, but for the finer details I'm just guessing :/ Anyone know if there is anything better than these?

I do not know, maybe this,

http://andegraf.com/rockets/n1.htm

PS.very beautiful model !!!
Here are some photos including the upper two stages from the bottom, which seems pretty rare.
Have you seen Astronautix yet? Or are you using Astronautix as the source.....?
